main event: A civilian observed an unidentified flying object in Williams, Minnesota on December 17, 1968 for approximately 25 minutes.
interesting points: The observer reported a blue trail associated with the object lasting at least 3 hours and 25 minutes., The report comes from Project Blue Book, a historical U.S. Air Force program., The observer used low power binoculars for viewing the object., The object was described as slightly larger than a star and green in color., No photographs or physical evidence were documented in the report.
